thority tendering on a daily basis. From my direct experience and from feedback gleaned from colleagues involved in local authority tendering support; I estimate social value questions appear in only half of ITTs and that and even where PSSVA compliant procurement exist they are  partial and stop gap. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I have worked on tenders in Scotland where the PSSVA equivalent, Community Benefits, has been up and running for some time. There are I feel lessons that could be learned from their approach to embedding Community Benefit clauses into public sector procurement. There are also some excellent examples of English local authorities that have progressed PSSVA on a strategic level.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I would also comment that PSSVA thinking is yet to be fully integrated into national public sector procurement; NHS and in other areas such as Clinical Commissioning Groups.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Public sector bodies must pay attention to:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Developing a policy for Social Value (SV) commissioning and procurement. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Translating policies into verifiable requirements within a tender specification. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Developing weighting to be applied to contribution to social value criteria.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Developing Social Value criteria to judge the most advantageous tender.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Embedding Social Value into sustainable commissioning strategies.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Linking Social Value to corporate plans and sustainable communities’ strategy.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Engaging supplier communities to prepare them for Social Value procurement.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Pre-procurement market-testing enabling SV consultation with potential contractors</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Monitoring and performance management based on Social Value outcomes. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 11.25pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Managing contracts to maximise realisation of Social Value. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 11.25pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:3.75pt 0pt 11.25pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>